    "body": "Suppose $T: \\mathbb{R}^{2} \\rightarrow \\mathbb{R}^{2}$ is a linear transformation and $A=\\left[\\begin{array}{ll}1 & 1 \\\\ 0 & 2\\end{array}\\right]$ is the standard matrix for $T$. Let $\\mathbf{u}=\\left[\\begin{array}{c}-1 \\\\ 1\\end{array}\\right], \\mathbf{v}=\\left[\\begin{array}{l}1 \\\\ 2\\end{array}\\right]$. Consider the following statements:\n(i) $T(\\mathbf{u})=\\left[\\begin{array}{c}-1 \\\\ 1\\end{array}\\right]$,\n(ii) $T(2 \\mathbf{u}+\\mathbf{v})=2 T(\\mathbf{u})+T(\\mathbf{v})$,\n(iii) $T(\\mathbf{x})=A \\mathbf{x}$ for any $\\mathbf{x} \\in \\mathbb{R}^{2}$.\n\n\nWhich of the above statements is/are true?",
    "solution": [
